Are Andorra and Luxembourg EU Members?

Andorra and Luxembourg are not members of the European Union. They are states that cooperate with the European Union and therefore play significant roles in helping other member-states, since they are small states.

There are, however, East African countries that are member of EU states like Eritrea and Djibouti. The Republic of Macedonia is also a member of the EU, as well as Cyprus.

Others are Greenland, Madeira, Falkland Islands, and Shetland Islands. The little known ACT (Australia, New Zealand, and UK) is also a member.
